        "content": "<p>If this is lean 4 code, the lowercase <code>mathlib</code> might be causing you problems elsewhere. If you're dealing with something like list that has a well developed API, there will usually be a lemma (or series of lemmas) to get what you need if it's not exotic. <code>apply?</code> is a good way to test the waters.</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">import</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Mathlib</span>\n\n<span class=\"kn\">theorem</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">nonsense</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ℕ</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"bp\">^</span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">∈</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"o\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"o\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">→</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"k\">fun</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">h_mem</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=&gt;</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"c1\">-- click the link in the goal view to expand it to the application of what was found</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"k\">have</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">h_disj</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"bp\">^</span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">∨</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"bp\">^</span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">apply?</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"gr\">sorry</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>There's a dependent elimination thing in this example that apparently makes the obvious answer of just 'cases' a little bit complicated, but the API provided by these lemmas is there to try and minimize the extent to which that bleeds through into and interferes with day to day use.</p>",
